All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Ball
The Ball class represents a ball object in the game.
BallManager
The BallManager class manages the behavior and movements of the ball in the game.
Game
The Game class represents a game environment with its properties and functionalities.
GameController
The GameController class controls the flow of the game, including managing scenes, game loop, and handling events.
GameMenu
The GameMenu class represents the menu of the game.
GameView
The GameView class represents the visual representation of the game.
KeyboardListener
The KeyboardListener class handles keyboard input for controlling the rackets in the game.
Main
The Main class serves as the entry point for the Ping Pong Game application.
MenuListener
The MenuListener class handles actions triggered by menu items in the game menu.
Player
The Player class represents a player in a game.
Racket
The Racket class represents a game racket that extends Rectangle and implements Resizable.
Resizable
The Resizable interface represents an object that can be resized along the x and y axes.
